HEADWORD: Chatelaine
<hw>Chat"e*laine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ch⟦acir⟧telaine</ets> the wife of a castellan, the mistress of a
chateau, a chatelaine chain.]</ety> <def>An ornamental hook, or brooch
worn by a lady at her waist, and having a short chain or chains attached
for a watch, keys, trinkets, etc. Also used adjectively; <as>as, a
<ex>chatelaine</ex> chain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

